# InfiniSynapse Core Rules

- Read `AGENTS.md` first; locate endpoints in `docs/reference/api-index.md` and the SSE flow in `docs/reference/task-lifecycle.md`.
- Search `upstream-docs/infinisynapse-site/zh/markdown/` before using an endpoint; English docs are supplemental only. Do not invent endpoints.
- Keep API Key server-side; never put it in frontend/mobile bundles. Default to a backend proxy route.
- Route AI calls by workload: non-agentic Q&A, summaries, rewrites, classification, extraction, and lightweight scoring should use a server-side LLM gateway; agentic long tasks, Browser Use, tool-heavy research, and workspace artifacts should use InfiniSynapse.
- Connect `GET /api/ai/events?connId=` before `POST /api/ai/message` (newTask).
- Use workspace APIs for deliverables: `getTaskWorkspace`, `previewFile`, `downloadTaskFile`.
- Download endpoints return binary streams — do not parse them as `{code,message,data}` JSON.
- Two upload kinds differ: `/api/ai/upload` (respond to Agent) vs `/api/tools/taskUpload` (proactively archive).
- For private deployment, check `AUTHING_SERVER_URL` first (var name, browser-reachable, bare `/api`, no trailing slash).
- Copyable reference clients live in `samples/sdk/`.
